The paper deals with a graph coloring problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of fast Fourier transform (FFT) to solve the problem is a technique commonly used in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also mentions improving bounds for the traveling salesman problem and counting perfect matchings, which are both topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves constraints on graphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT).
